Fresh Pi session: CODE REVIEW.

Inputs:
- User prompt: {{run.dir}}/prompt/prompt.md
- Design: {{run.dir}}/design/design.md
- Execution summary: {{run.dir}}/execution/summary-{{run.round}}.md
- Regression-testing report: {{run.dir}}/manual-testing/report-{{run.round}}.md
- Worktree: {{run.worktree-dir}}
- Base branch: {{inputs.base-branch}}

The current working directory is the isolated worktree. Review changes there.

Goal:
Review the implementation against the prompt and design and explicitly pass or fail it.

Rules:
- Do not edit source code, commit, push, or create a pull request.
- Review the diff against the base branch when available.
- Read and verify the regression-testing report.
- Check correctness, regressions, tests, security, maintainability, and whether changes are focused.
- Produce only concrete, actionable findings. Do not fail for missing screenshots or optional visual-review evidence.
- Pass when the implementation is acceptable. On failure, write issues for the next execution round.

Write:
- Report: {{run.dir}}/review/report-{{run.round}}.md
- Status: {{run.dir}}/review/status-{{run.round}}.json
- If failing: {{run.dir}}/review/issues-{{run.round}}.json

Status examples:
{"status":"pass","summary":"code review passed","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"code review found issues","issues_file":"review/issues-{{run.round}}.json"}
